om|title=Voodoo|artist=D'Angelo|type=album|award=Silver|relyear=2000}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|title=Voodoo|artist=D'Angelo|type=album|award=Platinum|relyear=2000}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[The 500 Greatest Albums of All Time]]\n* [[List of number-one albums of 2000 (U.S.)]]\n* [[Soulquarians]]\n* [[The Soultronics]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== Bibliography ==\n* {{cite book| author = Chris Jisi | title = Brave New Bass: Interviews and Lessons with the Innovators, Trendsetters and Visionaries | publisher = [[Hal Leonard Corporation]] | year = 2003 | location = | isbn = 0-87930-763-3}}\n* {{cite book | author1 = Ashyia N. Henderson | author2 = David G. Oblender | title = Contemporary Black Biography: Profiles Form the International Black Community | others = Vol. 27 | publisher = [[Gale Group]] | year = 2001 | location =  | isbn = 0-7876-4618-0 | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/contemporaryblac00hend }}\n* {{cite book| author = Clifford Thompson | title = Current Biography Yearbook | url = https://archive.org/details/currentbiography1969thom | url-access = registration | others = Vol. 62, No. 5 | publisher = [[H. W. Wilson Company|The H.W. Wilson Company]] | year = 2001 | location = | isbn = 0-8242-1016-6}}\n* {{cite book| author = Trevor Schoonmaker| title = Fela: From West Africa to West Broadway| publisher = [[Macmillan Publishers|Macmillan]]| year = 2003| location = | isbn = 1-4039-6210-3| url-access = registration| url = https://archive.org/details/felafromwestafri00bada}}\n* {{cite book|editors=Brackett, Nathan, Hoard, Christian|title=[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide|The New Rolling Stone Album Guide]]|others=Completely Revised and Updated 4th Edition|publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]]|date=November 1, 2004|isbn=0-7432-0169-8}}\n* {{cite book| author = [[Peter Shapiro (journalist)|Peter Shapiro]], Al Spicer | title = The Rough Guide to Soul and R&B | publisher = [[R